                        <h3 class="slug"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/">Goats and Soda</a></h3>
                </div>

            <h2 class="title"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2020/04/13/831883560/can-a-coronavirus-patient-who-isnt-showing-symptoms-infect-others"  data-metrics='{"action":"Click Story Title","category":"Story List"}' >What We Know About The Silent Spreaders Of COVID-19</a></h2>
            
            
            <p class="teaser"><a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2020/04/13/831883560/can-a-coronavirus-patient-who-isnt-showing-symptoms-infect-others"><time datetime="2020-04-13"><span class="date">April 13, 2020 &#149; </span></time>Some cases of the novel coronavirus are asymptomatic, presymptomatic or mildly symptomatic. Scientists are trying to determine their role in transmission of the disease.</a></p>

            

        </div>
        
