   <article class="item has-image">
    <div class="item-image">
        <div class="imagewrap" data-crop-type="wide">
    <a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2020/04/10/829890635/why-there-so-many-different-guidelines-for-face-masks-for-the-public" data-metrics='{"action":"Click Story Image","category":"Story List"}' >
        <img src="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/04/08/gettyimages-1208478104_wide-d0b2ef3461ab4e982325b7808ffbea5d260db51b-s300-c15.jpg" data-original="https://media.npr.org/assets/img/2020/04/08/gettyimages-1208478104_wide-d0b2ef3461ab4e982325b7808ffbea5d260db51b-s300.jpg" class="respArchListImg lazyOnLoad"  alt="Why There Are So Many Different Guidelines For Face Masks For The Public" />
    </a>
</div>
<div class="credit-caption">
    <div class="caption-wrap">
        <div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption">
            <p>
                A do-it-yourself mask culture is springing up in the Czech Republic. This woman was photographed on the Charles Bridge in Prague on March 28.
                
                <b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit">
                    
                    Michal Cizek/AFP via Getty Images
                    
                </b>
                <b class="hide-caption"><b>hide caption</b></b>
